<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Larva of Emplectonema viride collected from plankton in Charleston, OR, on 17 Oct 2013. Same individual is shown in two focal planes to highlight apical tuft (upper left, A) and posterior cirrus (lower right, A) and green epidermal pigment (B). Note paired subepidermal eyes, which are anterior to cerebral organs. Scale bar: 100 μm." , "Figure 4. Photomicrography of egg (A) and sperm (B) of Emplectonema viride. Scale bars: 25 μm." , "Figure 3. Photomicrographs of Emplectonema viride (A-D) and Emplectonema gracile (E-H). Abbreviations: cerebral ganglia, cg; rhynchostomopore, rh; cerebral organ opening, co. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, E); 0.5 mm (B, F); 100 μm (D, H)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/531663" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/531662" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/531661" .

